## 4. ACCESSIBILITY CONTRACT (WCAG 2.1 AA ‚Äî MANDATORY from `accessibility-wcag`)

### 4.1 Non-Negotiable Requirements
| Criterion | Requirement |
|-----------|-------------|
| **Color Contrast** | 4.5:1 (text), 3:1 (large text/UI), 3:1 (focus rings) |
| **Keyboard Navigation** | All interactive elements reachable, operable, visible focus |
| **Focus Indicators** | Visible, 3:1 contrast, 2px minimum, NEVER `outline: none` |
| **Skip Link** | First focusable element, visible on focus |
| **Heading Structure** | Single `<h1>`, no skipped levels |
| **Landmarks** | `banner`, `main`, `contentinfo`, `navigation`, `search` |
| **Form Labels** | Every input has `<label for="">` or `aria-label` |
| **Error Handling** | `aria-invalid`, `aria-describedby` with error message |
| **Live Regions** | `aria-live="polite"` for dynamic updates |
| **Images** | `alt=""` for decorative, descriptive alt for content |
| **Touch Targets** | Minimum 44√ó44px (48√ó48px preferred) |
| **Zoom** | Functional at 200% zoom, no horizontal scroll |
| **Reduced Motion** | `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` disables non-essential motion |

### 4.2 Required ARIA Patterns
```html
<!-- Button with loading state -->
<button aria-busy="true" aria-live="polite" disabled>Loading...</button>

<!-- Disclosure (accordion) -->
<button aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="panel-id">Trigger</button>
<div id="panel-id" hidden>Content</div>

<!-- Dialog (native <dialog> preferred) -->
<dialog aria-modal="true" aria-labelledby="dialog-title">
  <h2 id="dialog-title">Title</h2>
  <button aria-label="Close" autofocus>√ó</button>
</dialog>

<!-- Navigation -->
<nav aria-label="Primary navigation">
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/" aria-current="page">Home</a></li>
  </ul>
</nav>
```

### 4.3 Testing Requirements (MANDATORY)
- axe-core: 0 violations
- Lighthouse Accessibility: 100
- Keyboard-only: Complete task flow
- Screen Reader: NVDA/VoiceOver ‚Äî all content announced
- Color Contrast: All combinations pass

